The project in 2021 will mainly further focus on digitalization of Employment agency. 
The accent will also be on following activities: 
- The internal and external procedures of the Employment Service to be revised to respond to Covid-19 (including basic steps towards digitization);
- Through the capacity building program of the Employment Service and the Ministry of Labor and Social Welfare, an innovative intervention to be designed (with special emphasis on young people);
- A better-adapted framework for vocational rehabilitation and employment of persons with disabilities to be created;
- An action plan for interoperability of databases to be developed (Employment Agency, Tax Administration, Pension Fund, Center for Social Work, MUPJU and databases related to education)
- Updated policy impact assessments and responses to the Covid-19 crisis will be published late February 2021 by the Social Council.

